# To setup the CuPy package on ERDA you should run the following command once in a Jupyter notebook session:

conda install cupy

# If you would like to run with Numba you also need to install it with

conda install numba

# The conda installation(s) have to be done once every time you get a new virtual machine.
 
# You can test that CuPy is properly installed with the following commands.
# They should as output give some information about the available GPU
python -c "import cupy as cp; print(cp.__version__); print(cp.cuda.runtime.getDeviceProperties(0)['name'])"
python -c 'import cupy; cupy.show_config()'
